Switching between classes and coding sessions, or trying out other applications, isn't always easy.

For this example,
I'm offering a linear TI-89 script that will reset configuration settings.
This is a (roughly) factory configuration,
( More secure to manipulate than Memory Menu )

You can then easily change every settîngs to your own. As you develop your own applications, your script will become almost unnecessary. 

I hope you'll find it useful to insert `customkil()` somewhere between your own settings.
